article.headline: George Mason 76, Morehead State 65
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Lamar Butler scored 27 of his career-high 36 points in the first half as George Mason beat Morehead State 76-65 Thursday night. The Patriots (6-4) used a Butler jumper to build a 37-18 advantage with 4:50 remaining in the first half. George Mason led at the break 42-28. Trailing 50-32 early in the second half, Morehead State (6-5) chipped away at the George Mason lead but could get no closer than seven. Butler finished the night 12-of-20 from the field, including 6-of-12 from 3-point range, and 6-of-7 from the free throw line. Tony Skinn added 13 points for the Patriots. Will Thomas had 10 rebounds. Quinton Smith scored 21 points to lead the Eagles. Josh Reed finished with 16, while Chad McKnight and Jonathan True scored 10 each. George Mason outrebounded Morehead State 42-31, which included 17-10 on the offensive boards.
